HEADWORD: Simony
<hw>Sim"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>simonie</ets>, LL. <ets>simonia</ets>, fr. <ets>Simon</ets> Magus,
who wished to purchase the power of conferring the Holy Spirit.
<ets>Acts</ets> viii.]</ety> <def>The crime of buying or selling
ecclesiastical preferment; the corrupt presentation of any one to an
ecclesiastical benefice for money or reward.</def> <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

